# VIG AV — Oddo BHF Corporates & Markets — 28 May 2026
Q1 first take: strong insurance revenue, modest EBT miss; **Neutral** and **TP €62.0** confirmed, EPS estimates unchanged.

## What changed

No estimate revisions in the note — Oddo keeps EPS unchanged and confirms Neutral / TP €62.0.

| Metric | FY26E | FY27E | FY28E |
|--------|-------|-------|-------|
| Adj. EPS (€, Oddo) | 6.98 | 7.47 | 8.25 |
| Rating | Neutral (confirmed) | — | — |
| Target price | €62.0 (confirmed) | — | — |

Consensus EPS vs Oddo not stated in the extracted estimate picture. Oddo’s 2026E EBT is €1.25bn vs FactSet €1.28bn (company outlook €1.25–1.30bn, ex-NÜRNBERGER).

## Why it changed, and why now

This is a **Q1 2026 results first take**. Insurance revenue rose 9% y-o-y to €3,425m (ahead of Oddo’s €3,334m); EBT rose 19% to €310m but missed Oddo’s €325m (−5%), which Oddo links to investment-portfolio effects from Middle East market volatility (to be checked on the call). Combined ratio (COR) improved to 91.8% (vs Oddo 92.7%). [Valuation](file:///C:/Users/Andrey/Downloads/PDF-Info-extract-v1/.find-rpt/highlights/20260528_Oddo%20BHF%20Corporates%20%26%20Markets_0704de1259c4cfde1ea35_p1_c2.pdf#page=1)

Management reiterated the 2026 EBT outlook (€1.25–1.30bn ex-NÜRNBERGER). Oddo flags that last year’s NatCat run-rate was light vs history and that weather claims could rise later, especially in Q3; NÜRNBERGER regulatory approvals are in, with consolidated figures only from H2 2026. [Drivers](file:///C:/Users/Andrey/Downloads/PDF-Info-extract-v1/.find-rpt/highlights/20260528_Oddo%20BHF%20Corporates%20%26%20Markets_0704de1259c4cfde1ea35_p1_c1.pdf#page=1)

Context: results review / first take. Management contact: conference call at 15:00 CET (registration required).

